  <refnamediv>
    <refname>prbs</refname>
    <refpurpose>Generation of a pseudo-random number sequence</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   b = prbs(n)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>n:</term>
      <listitem><para> number of bits to generate</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>b:</term>
      <listitem><para> output binary vector (1 column of n elements, of value either 0 or 1)</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
The implementation is based on the <vardec>grand</vardec> Scilab generator.
   </para>
   <para>
Note: So as to generate always the same pseudo-"random" sequence, one can
initialize the seed of the random generator using the following command:
<varname>grand("setsd", n)</varname>, with n being any integer.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
// Generation of a vector of 10 random bits
b = prbs(10)

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

